{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17583511","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17583511"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T07:17:30+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T07:17:30+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"11644"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"11644","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/11644"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0,0.11,0.15,0.26,0.48]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"4270"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80127"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"4270","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4270"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"11644"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65404"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"40"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"5609"},{"type":"tags","id":"8761"},{"type":"tags","id":"10476"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"5737"},{"type":"contributions","id":"6897"},{"type":"contributions","id":"26975"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80127","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/80127"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe average, healthy adult takes in about 2L of fluid a day and that is balanced in loss by: \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003Eurine output: 1.6L \u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003Eperspiration: 0.2L \u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003Efaeces: 0.2L \u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThese are all approximate figures and will vary with the individual\u0027s immediate environment and their activities. If 2L are taken by mouth and 0.2L passed per rectum, the remaining 1.8L must be absorbed somewhere in the digestive tract. \u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"From which of the following sites is most fluid absorbed from the gut lumen?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Stomach","Duodenum","Jejunum","Ileum","Colon"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EAs well as approximately 2L of ingested fluid, the intestinal system is responsible for absorbing some 7L of other secretions. About 80% of this fluid absorption occurs in the small intestine, and the remaining 20% occurs in the colon. Most of this absorption occurs in the proximal small bowel - the jejunum. Absorption occurs mostly through osmosis, with epithelial cells of the gastrointestinal tract establishing a osmotic gradient through electrolyte transport through the cell.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe stomachs main role is the secretion of gastric juices, digestion, and controlled delivery of gastric contents to the rest of the gastrointestinal tract. The stomach absorbs little, if any fluid. While some absorption occurs in the \u003Cstrong\u003Eduodenum\u003C/strong\u003E, the \u003Cstrong\u003Ejejunum and ileum\u003C/strong\u003E are much longer and have a greater surface area, and therefore contribute more to fluid absorption. The surface area of the jejunum is increased by the presence of microvilli. The distal ileum has less microvilli and plays less of a role in fluid absorption, but has an important role in the absorption of some specific solutes.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The majority of fluid absorption in the GIT occurs in the small intestine - particularly the jejunum"],"references":["Barrett, K. Gastrointestinal Physiology. 2nd ed. McGraw Hill; 2014.","Costanzo L. Physiology. 5th ed. Philadelphia: Saunders; 2014.","Silverthorn D. Human Physiology. 8th ed. Pearson; 2019."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65404"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"11644"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65404","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/65404"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-17T16:09:31+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-17T16:10:19+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"4270"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80127"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"40","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/40"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\u2699\ufe0f","name":"Physiology","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"4"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships